Collections are arranged into groups for searching. Click on a group name to search the collections in that group. A collection may include some content outside of the group's definition, and a collection could appear in more than one group. Click the title of a specific collection to search it alone. Sometimes it is advantageous to search a single collection. For example, search field and sorting options are often specific to the collection, allowing for a more refined search.

Some collections have a very narrow focus. Other collections are broader, and may encompass many sub-collections. Occassionally an image appears in multiple collections, though generally there is a single authoritative source for each image.

item.p: Matching words: The search engine attempts to match any word or phrase exactly as you put it in the box.
e.g.: Picasso and Rembrandt in a box will look for
Punctuation: All punctuation is treated as an empty space.
Case: The search engine is not case sensitive.
Wildcards: Use wildcard * to expand word stems. This is a good way to search for variations on a word.
Choose image collections: Limit your search to only those collections you choose in the image collections list.

Result.ItemDescription: Normandia ducatus / Henricus Hondius excudit.

Values.Value: Includes the coat of arms of France and Normandy while the title cartouche is framed by vines of fruit and the scale cartouche is framed by two cherubs.
This state was published in atlases by Jan Jansson in 1636 and 1637.
From the Jansson Appendix Atlas 1636-1680, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan.

Result.ItemDescription: Africae nova tabula / auct. Jud. Hondio.

Values.Value: Africae nova tabula / auct. Jud. Hondio.
Border includes views of 12 African cities and examples of local costumes, while the map includes illustrations of flying fish and sea monsters on the ocean and animals on the continent.
The title cartouche includes vines bearing fruit and a face, while the author cartouche has two young children, a skull within a clock topped with a bell, and the date 1623.

Values.Value: Nobilis fluvius Albis : maximâ curâ, ex variis, famosique Autoribus collectus, et in lucem editus / a Ioanne Ianssonio.
North oriented to the bottom of the map.

Includes inscription "Amplissimis, consutitissimis, et prudentissimis Viris Senatoribus, consulibusque Republcæ Hamburgensis hanc celeberrimi Fluminis Albis delineationem, summa studio ac nitor elaboratam, benevolo animo dat, dicat donat".
View of "Emporium Hamburgum" found in lower right of map. complete with an index of some of the buildings, crowned by a coat of arms of Hamburg.
Includes illustrations of cartographers working around the scale cartouche.

Result.ItemDescription: Nobilis Hannoniae com. descriptio / Auctore Iacobo Surhonio.

Values.Value: Nobilis Hannoniae com. descriptio / Auctore Iacobo Surhonio.
Engraving of Hannonii man and woman along right map border and two coats of arms above the title cartouche.
Insets: views of Mons and Valenchiennes.
The title cartouche states that the map was originally printed by Visscher in Harrlem in 1630.
'11' printed in lower right corner of map is missing in copy of Clark's 1617 "Germania Inferior" atlas.
